\set[name] {Abeloth}
\align {
	\block {
		Large Aberration, Lawful Evil
		\line
		\image[https://www.dndbeyond.com/avatars/thumbnails/0/11/1000/1000/636238825975375671.jpeg]
		\line
		\b{Armor Class}~17 (natural armor)\n
		\b{Hit Points}~135 \roll[18d10 + 36, desc: Hit Points]\n
		\b{Speed}~10ft, swim 40 ft\n
		\b{Initiative }~\roll[-1, desc: Initiative]
		\line
		\align {
			\align[vc] { \b{STR} 21 \roll[ 5, desc: Strength Check] }
			\align[vc] { \b{DEX}  9 \roll[-1, desc: Dexterity Check] }
			\align[vc] { \b{CON} 15 \roll[ 2, desc: Constitution Check] }
			\align[vc] { \b{INT} 18 \roll[ 4, desc: Intelligence Check] }
			\align[vc] { \b{WIS} 15 \roll[ 2, desc: Wisdom Check] }
			\align[vc] { \b{CHA} 18 \roll[ 4, desc: Charisma Check] }
		}
		\line
		\b{Saving Throws}~
		\roll[6, desc: Constitution Save]{CON}, 
		\roll[8, desc: Intelligence Save]{INT}, 
		\roll[6, desc: Wisdom Save]{WIS}\n

		\b{Skills}~
		History \roll[12, desc: History Check], 
		Perception \roll[10, desc: Perception Check]\n

		\b{Senses}~Darkvision 120 ft, Passive Perception 20\n

		\b{Languages}~Deep Speech, Telepathy 120 ft.\n

		\b{Challenge}~10 (5,900 XP)\n

		\b{Proficiency Bonus}~+4\n
		\line
		\h2[true]{Features}
		\box {
			\h3{Amphibious}
			The $name can breathe air and water
		}
		\n
		\box {
			\h3{Mucous Cloud} 
			While underwater, the $name is surrounded by transformative
			mucus. A creature that touches the $name or that hits it 
			with a melee attack while within 5 feet of it must make a 
			\save[14, type: CON]~saving throw. On a failure, the creature 
			is diseased for \roll[1d4]~hours. The diseased creature can breathe 
			only underwater.
		}
		\n
		\box { 
			\h3{Probing Telepathy} 
			If a creature communicates telepathically with the aboleth, the 
			aboleth learns the creature's greatest desires if the aboleth can 
			see the creature.
		}
	}
	\line
	\block {
		\h2[true]{Actions}
		\box { 
			\h3{Multiattack} 
			The $name makes three tentacle attacks
		}
		\n
		\box { 
			\h3{Tentacle} 
			Melee Weapon Attack: \roll[9, desc: Tentacle Attack]~to hit, reach 10 ft. one target. 
			Hit: 12 \roll[2d6 + 5, type: dmg, desc: Tentacle Damage]~bludgeoning damage.
			\line
			If the target is a creature, it must succeed on a \save[14, type: CON] 
			saving throw or become diseased. The disease has no effect for 1 
			minute and can be removed by any magic that cures disease. After 1 
			minute, the diseased creature's skin becomes translucent and slimy, 
			the creature can't regain hit points unless it is underwater, and the 
			disease can be removed only by heal or another disease-curing spell of 
			6th level or higher. When the creature is outside a body of water, it 
			takes \roll[1d12, type: dmg, desc: Disease Damage]~acid damage every 10 minutes unless
			moisture is applied to the skin before 10 minutes have passed.
		}
		\n
		\box { 
			\h3{Tail} 
			Melee Weapon Attack: \roll[9, desc: Tail Attack]~to hit, reach 10 ft. one target. 
			Hit: 15 \roll[3d6 + 5, type: dmg, desc: Tail Damage]~bludgeoning damage.
		}
		\n
		\box { 
			\h3{Enslave (3/Day)}
			The aboleth targets one creature it can see within 30 feet of it. The 
			target must succeed on a \save[14, type: WIS]~saving throw or be magically 
			charmed by the aboleth until the aboleth dies or until it is on a 
			different plane of existence from the target. The charmed target is 
			under the aboleth's control and can't take reactions, and the aboleth 
			and the target can communicate telepathically with each other over any 
			distance.

			Whenever the charmed target takes damage, the target can repeat the
			saving throw. On a success, the effect ends. No more than once every 24 
			hours, the target can also repeat the saving throw when it is at least 
			1 mile away from the aboleth.
		}
	}
}
\line
\h2{Description}
$name are a race of malevolent, eel-like aberrations with potent psionic abilities.
